notes: Deep funk speeds into dream-poppy alternative metal that swirls into a spacey jungle on a riverboat, passing random wooden posts nestled in trees and brush.
Travels through a funky desert into a Souq maze.
A ballroom overlooking the coast gets swept into a dust storm, spinning upward until it peaks above the clouds at the apex of its swing, then falls back -> Never Break.
Cliff diving from plane to plane on a sun-soaked California beach.
Fun, dancey grooving gets psychedelically anxious.

Slick grooving finds itself in a fiery monster truck rally that briefly calms before collectively moving into a gradual, patient buildup that escalates fiercely until the Birds of Prey come crashing down.

Rides up an escalator and through opaque doorways, leaving trails of dotted lasers behind as it weaves through an endless hallway, then slowly loses speed as the sandy floor swallows it, before finding a hopeful exit lit by a lone window, where it treacherously climbs back to the main theme.

Major saxophone solo before Jake from Dizgo hops on keys and speeds them through outer space toward anxious riffing that implodes powerfully and falls to earth in shoegazey fashion with great guitar work.
Double-time playing leads to a big buildup.

Crawls out of an extraction point and lays tracks of jungle before heating up, exploding, and trudging through dark, electronically charged fields and up a rugged mountainside in search of a distant light source.
Exits its shuttle’s pod into a verdant planet and falls into a rich, underground cave where it sinks into an amniotic tunnel and blooms with echo.
Dreams itself into a hazy bush and makes its way through an Anatolian maze.
